'''Ladislav Krejčí''' (born 20 April 1999) is a Czech professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] or [[midfielder]] for {{English football updater|WolverhW}} club [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]], on loan from {{Spanish football updater|Girona}} club [[Girona FC|Girona]], and [[Captain (association football)|captains]] the [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech Republic national team]].

In 2024, the Czech edition of [[Forbes]] featured Krejčí in their ''30 under 30'' list'': 30 of the most talented Czechs under 30 years old''.<ref name=forbes>{{cite web |title=30 pod 30: Forbes odhaluje mladé talenty roku 2024 |url=https://forbes.cz/30-pod-30-2024/ |website=Forbes.cz |publisher=Forbes Česko |date=5 February 2024 |language=cs |access-date=3 September 2025}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Zbrojovka Brno===
Krejčí made his professional debut for [[FC Zbrojovka Brno|Zbrojovka Brno]] in its home match against [[AC Sparta Prague|Sparta Prague]] on 2 October 2016, which ended in a 3–3 draw.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Série bez prohry nekončí, Spartě sebral vítězství Hyčka|url=http://www.fczbrno.cz/zapas.asp?id=Serie-bez-prohry-nekonci-Sparte-sebral-vitezstvi-Hycka-2375|website=Zbrojovka Brno|access-date=2 October 2016|language=cs}}</ref> He scored his first league goal on 13 May 2018 in Brno's 4–1 win at Teplice.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://fotbal.idnes.cz/brno-strelci-prvni-gol-ladislav-krejci-antonin-rusek-konstantin-bazeljuk-1rx-/fotbal.aspx?c=A180515_102739_fotbal_rou|title=První ligový gól? Euforie, radoval se brněnský mladík Krejčí|website=[[Mladá fronta Dnes]]|date=15 May 2018|access-date=15 May 2018|language=cs}}</ref>

===Sparta Prague===
On 6 June 2019, Krejčí signed a four-year contract with [[AC Sparta Prague|Sparta Prague]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Vacek|first=Jan|title=Třetí posila pro Spartu, Krejčí se upsal na čtyři roky. Velký posun, říká |url=https://isport.blesk.cz/clanek/fotbal-1-liga-rocnik-2019-20/364577/treti-posila-pro-spartu-krejci-se-upsal-na-ctyri-roky-velky-posun-rika.html|website=[[Blesk]]|publisher=[[Czech News Center]]|date=6 June 2019|access-date=28 May 2023|language=cs}}</ref> In July 2022, he became Sparta's captain, replacing [[Bořek Dočkal]] who had retired the previous season.<ref>{{cite news|title=Krejčí je novým kapitánem Sparty. Priske ocenil jeho přístup a kvalitu|url=https://isport.blesk.cz/clanek/fotbal-1-liga-rocnik-2022-23/417031/krejci-je-novym-kapitanem-sparty-priske-ocenil-jeho-pristup-a-kvalitu.html|website=[[Blesk]]|publisher=[[Czech News Center]]|date=18 July 2022|access-date=28 May 2023|language=cs}}</ref>

In May 2023, Krejčí helped the club to win its first championship title since 2014 as captain.<ref name="sport.cz 2023">{{Cite news|title=Sparta v euforii! Remíza na Slovácku odstartovala mistrovské oslavy|url=https://www.sport.cz/clanek/fotbal-ceska-1-liga-sparta-v-euforii-remiza-na-slovacku-odstartovala-mistrovske-oslavy-4229432|website=Sport.cz|date=23 May 2023|language=cs|publisher=Borgis}}</ref> He was awarded as the midfielder and player of the [[2022–23 Czech First League|2022–23]] season by the League Football Association.<ref>{{Cite press release|title=Záložníkem sezony se stal kapitán mistrů Krejčí, útočníkům kraluje střelec Řezníček|url=https://www.lfafotbal.cz/clanek/629-zaloznikem-sezony-se-stal-kapitan-mistru-krejci-utocnikum-kraluje-strelec-reznicek|website=League Football Association|date=25 May 2023|access-date=28 May 2023|language=cs}}</ref><ref>{{Cite press release|title=Hráčem sezony 2022/23 je Krejčí, mezi trenéry vládne Priske. Osobností ligy Jindřišek|url=https://www.lfafotbal.cz/clanek/634-hracem-sezony-2022-23-je-krejci-mezi-trenery-vladne-priske-osobnosti-ligy-jindrisek|website=League Football Association|date=27 May 2023|access-date=28 May 2023|language=cs}}</ref>

On 10 March 2024, Krejčí received his fifth red card in Sparta Prague jersey (in 4–0 away loss against [[FC Viktoria Plzeň|Viktoria Plzeň]]) and set the new record for most received red cards in Sparta Prague history in the league competition since 1954, supprasing [[Jiří Homola]] with four red cards.<ref>{{cite news|first=Jiří|last=Lizec|title=Tristní disciplína Sparty. Osmá červená v sezoně, Krejčí v čele historických statistik|url=https://www.sport.cz/clanek/fotbal-ceska-1-liga-tristni-disciplina-sparty-osma-cervena-v-sezone-krejci-na-cele-historickych-statistik-5024408|website=Sport.cz|publisher=Borgis|date=11 March 2024|language=cs}}</ref> In May that year, he helped the club to win its second championship title in two seasons,<ref name="blesk.cz 2024">{{Cite news|title=SESTŘIH: Boleslav - Sparta 0:5. Titul pro Letenské! Kuchta dal čtyři góly|url=https://isport.blesk.cz/clanek/fotbal-1-liga-rocnik-2023-24/447579/sestrih-boleslav-sparta-0-5-titul-pro-letenske-kuchta-dal-ctyri-goly.html|website=[[Blesk]]|date=18 May 2024|language=cs|publisher=[[Czech News Center]]|agency=[[Czech News Agency]]|access-date=19 May 2024}}</ref> and domestic cup as captain.<ref name="sport.cz 2024">{{Cite news|last=Neumann|first=Robert|title=Sparta slaví double! Triumf v nervózním finále trefil Birmančevič|url=https://www.sport.cz/clanek/fotbal-pohar-fotbaliste-sparty-budou-ve-finale-domaciho-poharu-v-plzni-usilovat-o-zisk-double-5028779|website=Sport.cz|date=22 May 2024|language=cs|publisher=Borgis|access-date=23 May 2024}}</ref>

===Girona===
On 14 June 2024, Krejčí signed a five-year contract with Spanish side [[Girona FC|Girona]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.gironafc.cat/en/news/ladislav-krejci-signed-for-5-seasons |title=Ladislav Krejčí, signed for 5 seasons |website=[[Girona FC]]|date=14 June 2024|access-date=14 June 2024}}</ref>

====Loan to Wolverhampton Wanderers====
On 28 August 2025, Krejčí joined [[Premier League]] club [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] on an initial season-long loan deal, joining on a four-year deal for a £26 million fee should certain clauses be met over the duration of the loan.<ref>{{cite web|last=Mashiter|first=Nick|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/c62w4e4ydxyo|title=Wolves sign defender Krejci on initial loan deal|website=BBC Sport|date=28 August 2025|accessdate=28 August 2025}}</ref> The move saw him become the first Czech player in the club's history.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wolves.co.uk/news/mens-first-team/20250828-krejci-becomes-latest-new-arrival/|title=Krejci becomes latest new arrival|website=[[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.]]|date=28 August 2025|accessdate=28 August 2025}}</ref>

==International career==
In March 2022, Krejčí received his first Czech senior call-up from coach [[Jaroslav Šilhavý]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=Krejčí ml.: Reprezentace byla vždy můj sen, jsem za nominaci vděčný|url=https://www.fotbal.cz/repre/krejci-ml-reprezentace-byla-vzdy-muj-sen-jsem-za-nominaci-vdecny/a16045|website=Football Association of the Czech Republic|date=22 March 2022|access-date=25 September 2023|language=cs}}</ref>

In the [[UEFA Euro 2024 qualifying]] match on 24 March 2023 against [[Poland national football team|Poland]], Krejčí scored his first goal which is considered to be the fastest in the Czech Republic national football team history.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Krejčí zaznamenal nejrychlejší gól fotbalové reprezentace od rozdělení federace|url=https://www.ceskenoviny.cz/zpravy/2343510|website=České noviny|date=24 March 2023|access-date=25 March 2023|language=cs}}</ref> On 17 June 2023, he scored another goal against [[Faroe Islands national football team|Faroe Islands]] resulting in a 3–0 victory.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Čeští fotbalisté vyhráli v kvalifikaci o ME na Faerských ostrovech 3:0|url=https://www.ceskenoviny.cz/zpravy/cesti-fotbaliste-vyhrali-v-kvalifikaci-o-me-na-faerskych-ostrovech-30/2379414|website=České noviny|date=17 June 2023|language=cs}}</ref> On 28 May 2024, he was named in the 26-man squad for the [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{cite news |date=28 May 2024 |title=Nominace reprezentace na přípravný kemp před EURO 2024 |trans-title=National team nominations for the preparatory camp before EURO 2024 |url=https://www.fotbal.cz/repre/nominace/nominace/836 |language=cs |publisher=[[Czech Football Association]] |access-date=28 May 2024}}</ref>

On 23 March 2026, Krejčí was confirmed as the new captain of the Czech Republic, after [[Tomáš Souček]]'s earlier dismissal.<ref>{{Cite news |agency=[[Czech News Agency]] |date=2026-03-23 |title=Česká reprezentace má nového kapitána. Do baráže o MS půjde s páskou Krejčí |trans-title=The Czech national team has a new captain. Krejčí will take the armband to the World Cup play-offs |url=https://www.denik.cz/fotbal/baraz-o-ms-ve-fotbale-cesko-kapitan-ladislav-krejci.html |access-date=2026-03-23 |work=[[Deník]] |language=cs|publisher=[[Vltava Labe Media]]}}</ref>

